Measure the diameter of each cylinder bore at the top of the piston ring travel at a right angle to the crankshaft ( "A", Figure 5.20
) and to the centerline of the crankshaft ( "B", Figure 5.20
). Record the readings and calculate the difference.

Cylinder bore taper is the difference between the cylinder bore diameters measured at the "Top" of ring travel ( Figure 5.21
) and the "Bottom" of ring travel ( Figure 5.21
) (AT RIGHT ANGLES TO THE CENTERLINE OF THE CRANKSHAFT).
